"{\"uid\": \"thestar.com.my-news-world-2024-08-04-olympics--ukraine-claims-1st-gold-at-paris-2024-in-fencing-women039s-sabre-team\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Sunday, 04 Aug 2024  PARIS, Aug. 3 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine came from behind to beat South Korea in the women's sabre team final, clinching the country's first gold at the Paris Olympic Games here on Saturday.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 204, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 47, \"end\": 54, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9480413912335178, \"rank\": 0.03690334482247324, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 80, \"end\": 91, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.7822524803022409, \"rank\": 0.2653846326570744, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olga Kharlan was no doubt the star of the night, coming into the final with a bronze from the individual event on Monday.\", \"from\": 206, \"to\": 327, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 206, \"end\": 218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olha_Kharlan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olga Kharlan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olha_Kharlan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olha_Kharlan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The five-time Olympian put Ukraine ahead after the first bout, but the South Koreans then overcame a slow start to take the lead.\", \"from\": 328, \"to\": 457, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 342, \"end\": 350, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999996742079096, \"rank\": 3.257922250351512e-07, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 355, \"end\": 362, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9480413912335178, \"rank\": 0.03690334482247324, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Entering the final bout with a three-point disadvantage, Kharlan held off the nerves to outscore Jeon Ha-young 8-2 en route to a 45-42 victory.\", \"from\": 459, \"to\": 602, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 33-year-old Ukrainian now has six Olympic medals under her name, including two team golds, one team silver, and three individual bronzes.\", \"from\": 603, \"to\": 744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 619, \"end\": 628, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.7672150077026204, \"rank\": 0.2737890295566724, \"text\": \"Ukrainian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Led by Misaki Emura, Japan defeated France, silver medalist from Tokyo, 45-40 in the bronze medal match to clinch its maiden women's sabre team medal at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 746, \"to\": 912, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 753, \"end\": 765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Misaki_Emura\", \"score\": 0.9999997066034187, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Misaki Emura\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Misaki_Emura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Misaki_Emura\"}, {\"begin\": 767, \"end\": 772, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 0.7167691483125567, \"rank\": 0.3748996896363098, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 782, \"end\": 788, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"sc